pr_body:
**Motivation**
Adding a "Collections‚Äù section to the extension would make users appreciate the sources available for them to choose from. They can explore what the sources have to offer and therefore would know what sources they should filter down if they want better results for their queries.

**Description**
The goal is to add a separate section with the display of the different sources and the ability to "search by collection".

Since CC-Vocabulary will be used for this section, the redesigning of major sections and components of the extension is inevitable for this goal. The extension currently uses a very outdated version of Vocabulary and almost everything will be updated with the new version. The adoption of CC-Vocabulary will be gradual and we need not focus on the details as the main goal is very different for this PR. For starters, I will be focusing on the Options page.

- [x] My pull request has a descriptive title (not a vague title like `Update

pr_title: Add new filters to the extension
pr_body:
**Description**
This PR adds more filters, supported by the Catalog API, to the extension. Very broadly there will be three objectives :
- add functioning, multi-select dropdowns for choosing the filters.
- modify the current workflow to incorporate the searching by new filters.
- Adding the new filters to the "filters" tab of the Options page so that default filters can be set.

**Checklist:**
- [ ] My pull request has a descriptive title (not a vague title like `Update
  index.md`).

pr_title: Cache the bookmarks data in local storage
pr_body:
**Description**
<!-- Add your description below. -->
Right now only the image id is stored as bookmark(which is used to get the image details from the API when rendering the bookmarks) and all the workflows related to the bookmarks depend on this. 
This PR will implement the caching of the bookmarks data and modify all the related workflows accordingly.

This PR also has the code that handles the migrations of bookmarks stored in the user's local storage to the new structure. The `import bookmarks` workflow is also modified to handle old bookmark files.

**Checklist:**
- [x] My pull request has a descriptive title (not a vague title like `Update
  index.md`).
- [x] My pull request targets the `master` branch of the repository.
- [x] My commit messages follow [best practices][best_practices].
- [ ] I added tests for the changes I made (if applicable).
- [ ] I added or updated documentation (if applicable).
- [x] I tried running the project locally and verified that there are no
  visible errors.

pr_title: Add Voluntary loading (Load more button) in the bookmarks section
pr_body:
**Description**
Currently, all the bookmarks are rendered altogether when we switch to the bookmarks section. For a large number of bookmarks, this creates a visible lag among other performance issues. Rendering only a part of the bookmarks gallery at the beginning and allowing to view more bookmarks by pressing the "Load more" button at the bottom seems like a good solution.

pr_title: Increase the maximum number of bookmarks that the extension can have
pr_body:
**Description**
<!-- Add your description below. -->
Sync storage is used to store bookmarks. There are very tight limitations on this storage that needs to be taken into account but the real bottleneck is caused by the cap of `8Kb` on the key value of the storage. After the last update where the bookmarks data was cached, the maximum number of bookmarks has come down to 51. 

This PR would increase the maximum number of bookmarks that a user can have on the extension. This would require a thorough review of the current bookmarks workflows, followed by significant changes and improvements.
